direction: right

*.style.border-radius: 8
*.style.font-size: 13
*.style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
*.style.stroke: "#333333"

# --- Entry ---

entry: |md
  **docs-review-modular-docs**

  - .adoc file input
  - Red Hat modular docs
  - checklist review
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Type identification (decision) ---

identify-type: |md
  **Identify module type**

  concept / procedure /
  reference / assembly?
| {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Module-type checklists container ---

checklists: Module-type checklists {
  style.fill: "#ececec"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2

  concept: |md
    **Concept**

    - noun-phrase title
    - anchor `_{context}`
    - overview intro
    - no step-by-step
  |
  procedure: |md
    **Procedure**

    - imperative title
    - anchor `_{context}`
    - `.Procedure` steps
    - allowed sections order
  |
  reference: |md
    **Reference**

    - noun-phrase title
    - anchor `_{context}`
    - tables / labeled lists
    - logical ordering
  |
  assembly: |md
    **Assembly**

    - anchor, NO `_{context}`
    - `:context:` set
    - `include::` leveloffset
    - next / resources order
  |
}

# --- Attribute validation ---

attribute-check: |md
  **Attribute check**

  - find `{attr}` refs
  - locate `:attr:` defs
  - skip built-ins
  - flag undefined
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Common violations ---

violations: |md
  **Common violations**

  - wrong vs correct table
  - missing leveloffset
  - custom subheadings
  - module includes module
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Classify ---

classify: |md
  **Classify issues**

  - required (violations)
  - [SUGGESTION]
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Report ---

report: |md
  **Report**

  - issues list
  - required vs suggested
  - vale (optional)
| {
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#f5f5f5"
  style.stroke: "#333333"
  style.stroke-width: 2
}

# --- Flow ---

entry -> identify-type
identify-type -> checklists: "matched type"
checklists -> attribute-check
attribute-check -> violations
violations -> classify
classify -> report
